{"id":720,"parent_id":0,"book_id":8,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":720,"title":"Joppa","subtitle":"","short_title":"Joppa","uri":"/scriptures/bd/joppa","content":[["div",{"id":"t1","uri":"/scriptures/bd/joppa.t1","order":".000.1864"},[".title","Joppa"],["div",{"id":"p1","uri":"/scriptures/bd/joppa.p1","order":".000.1865"},"(Modern",["i","Jaffa."],") A town on the southwest coast of Palestine, the nearest port to Jerusalem (called “Japho” in",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/josh/19.46"},"Josh. 19:46"],"). It became a place of importance as a harbor in Solomon’s reign (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/2-chr/2.16"},"2 Chr. 2:16"],"; see also",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/ezra/3.7"},"Ezra 3:7"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/jonah/1.3"},"Jonah 1:3"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/acts/9.36-43"},"Acts 9:36–43"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/acts/10.5,8,23,32"},"10:5, 8, 23, 32"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/acts/11.5"},"11:5"],"). In New Testament times it was the only town on the coast that was more Jewish than Gentile."]]],"refs":null}
